Questions: What is my student ID number?
Answers: Your student’s identification includes a 9 digit University Identification Number (UID) on the Redbird Card and a separate 10 digit billing ID (EMPL ID) on the statement. Either number can be used to access account details.

Questions: How do I pay for my textbooks?
Answers: Textbooks are considered an out of pocket expense and are not billed through the university. They must be purchased at the campus bookstore or online.

Questions: I’m helping my student pay—how do I access their account?
Answers: Parents or other payers should be added as Authorized Users. This grants secure online access to view billing details, make payments, set up payment plans, and receive notifications without exposing academic records.

Questions: Why am I being charged Student Health Insurance?
Answers: Eligible students (those registering for 9 or more credit hours in fall/spring or 6 in summer) are automatically assessed a health insurance fee to ensure worldwide coverage. A waiver is available if alternate coverage is provided.

Questions: What is the Financial Responsibility Agreement (FRA)?
Answers: The FRA is a signed acknowledgment that the student is responsible for all incurred charges (tuition, fees, etc.) for the semester. It must be completed before registration; otherwise, a hold is placed on the account.

Questions: Why do I have a hold on my account?
Answers: Holds may occur for reasons such as unpaid balances, returned checks, or an incomplete FRA. Specific details can be viewed by logging into My.IllinoisState.

Questions: How do I get information for employer reimbursement?
Answers: Billing statements, payment records, and grade details are available through the online billing portal and Student Service Center. Follow the Tuition Reimbursement Requirements guide for complete instructions.

Questions: What if my student has a tuition sponsor?
Answers: The sponsor must submit verification (a letter, voucher, or similar documentation) to the Student Accounts Office before any third?party payment is processed.

Questions: Where can I cash a check from Illinois State University?
Answers: Refund and payroll checks (up to $300) can be cashed at the Cashiers Office in the Student Accounts Building.

Questions: How much do tuition and fees cost?
Answers: Tuition is charged on a per credit hour basis with additional mandatory fees—and for some programs, differential tuition. Detailed rates and fee structures are available on the Billing & Tuition Information page.

Questions: Why am I paying more for certain programs?
Answers: Differential tuition applies to programs that offer enhanced facilities, specialized instruction, or extra scholarship opportunities.

Questions: What are mandatory fees and why must they be paid?
Answers: Mandatory fees cover administrative costs for services provided to all students and are a required component of the overall cost of attendance.

Questions: Why do I need to pay the Outreach – FCR fees?
Answers: For some specialized programs, these fees cover the costs of delivering off campus or online instruction. Students assessed this fee are not automatically charged student insurance unless they opt in.

Questions: Why is my student charged tuition and fees for an internship?
Answers: Even off campus internships incur administrative and supervision costs; hence, tuition is assessed when credit is received.

Questions: What is Tuition Insurance/Protection (GradGuard)?
Answers: Tuition insurance protects your investment by reimbursing tuition, housing, and fees if a student must withdraw mid?semester for a covered reason. It complements the university’s refund policy.

Questions: Are housing, meal, and tuition charges on the same bill?
Answers: Yes. All charges are itemized on one online billing statement, though they are shown as separate line items.

Questions: How do I view my bill?
Answers: Bills (on?demand statements) become available via the online billing portal on set release dates (e.g., August 1 for fall, January 1 for spring, May 1 for summer).

Questions: How do I access my account balance?
Answers: The account balance is viewable through the online billing portal in My.IllinoisState. Authorized Users have the same access privileges.

Questions: How do I make a payment?
Answers: Payments can be made online, by mail, or in person. Online methods include credit card payments (with a convenience fee), direct deposit, or payment plan options.

Questions: Can I pay my bill with a credit card?
Answers: Yes, credit card payments are accepted through the online portal, though a convenience fee applies.

Questions: What happens if my payment is late or my account is overdue?
Answers: Late payments may result in additional fees, account holds that block registration, and eventual collections efforts.

Questions: Where do I send 529 Savings Plan checks?
Answers: 529 Savings Plan checks should be sent directly to the Student Accounts Office.

Questions: Which payment plan should I use if a 529 plan is involved?
Answers: The appropriate plan depends on whether the 529 covers the full balance or leaves a remainder. Detailed guidance is available on the 529 Plans page.

Questions: What should I do about scholarship checks or inquiries?
Answers: For scholarship-related questions or mailing instructions, please refer to the Scholarships page on the ISU website.

Questions: Why would my student receive a refund?
Answers: Refunds are issued when overpayments occur (for example, if financial aid exceeds current charges) or when adjustments are made after payment.

Questions: Will my student receive a refund if a course is dropped or they withdraw?
Answers: Refund eligibility depends on the timing of the withdrawal and the applicable charges. See the University Registrar’s guidelines and Course/Withdrawal policies for details.

Questions: When will my refund be issued?
Answers: Refund processing begins before classes start. eRefunds are typically posted on designated refund days (often Friday), and paper checks are mailed shortly thereafter.

Questions: How is my refund delivered?
Answers: Refunds are issued either by direct deposit (eRefund) or via a mailed paper check to the registered address.

Questions: Where do Parent PLUS loan refunds go?
Answers: Parent PLUS loan refunds are sent to the borrower’s mailing address unless excess funds are released directly to the student.

Questions: Why does my Student Refund appear as a charge on my account?
Answers: Due to accounting practices balancing debits and credits, refunds are recorded in the “charges” column to maintain an accurate account balance.

Questions: How is financial aid applied to my student’s account?
Answers: Once processed, financial aid is applied to the current term’s charges. Any remaining balance must be paid with personal funds or other financing.

Questions: What should I do if financial aid isn’t showing up on the account?
Answers: Verify that all requirements on the My.IllinoisState To Do List are completed. If problems persist, contact the Financial Aid Office.

Questions: Can next semester’s financial aid be used for the current term?
Answers: No. Financial aid applies only to the semester for which it is awarded.

Questions: How do international students pay via TransferMate?
Answers: International payments are made by logging into the student account, selecting TransferMate INTL from the payment options, reviewing the applicable rate, and following the instructions.

Questions: What fees does TransferMate charge?
Answers: International transactions via TransferMate are free, while domestic transactions incur a fee of $20.

Questions: How do I know if my TransferMate payment was successful?
Answers: Successful payments are confirmed by email and appear in the Payment History once pending transactions are cleared.

Questions: Can family members or Authorized Users access my student’s account?
Answers: Yes. Authorized Users can view billing details and make payments but cannot access academic records or saved payment methods.

Questions: What should I do if I notice a billing error or discrepancy?
Answers: Contact the Student Accounts Office immediately using the contact information provided on the billing portal or website to resolve any discrepancies.

Questions: How do I update my student’s personal information on their account?
Answers: Changes should be made via My.IllinoisState or by contacting the appropriate campus office. Keeping information updated is essential for receiving accurate billing and notifications.

Questions: When does class registration begin for the upcoming semester?
Answers: Course registration for the Fall 2025 semester is scheduled to begin on Monday, March 24, 2025, at 8:30 a.m.
